Key.Original: The Ares Modules have informative icons in the module tree.%1The most common are described here: %1%1 This module can be placed anywhere. %1 This modul has to be placed on units. %1 This can be placed either on a unit or anywhere. The module options avaiable depend on the choice! %1 This module has to be placed on an object but can often also include units. %1 This can be placed either on an object or anywhere. The module options avaiable depend on the choice! %1 The module is activated at the selected position.
For modules applied on objects or units it is often the case that you can either place it on one unit or place it elsewhere to apply it to multiple units.

Some modules have the option to select objects on which it is apply to. %1Whenever you hear this sound you can select objects and submit the selection by pressing %3[ENTER]%4. %1You can cancle the selection mode with %3[ESCAPE]%4.
Key.French: Il y a des modules qui avez l'option de choisir des objects à qui le module est employé. %1Chaque fois que vous écoutez ce signal, vous pouvez choisir des objects et confirmer le choix par appuyer sur la touche %3[ENTRÉE]%4. %1Vous pouvez abandonner le mode de choix par appuyer sur la touche %3[ECHAP]%4.
Key.German: Einige Module haben die Option Objekte auszuwählen auf die das Modul angewendet werden soll. %1Immer wenn du dieses Signal hörst, kannst du Objekte auswählen und die Auswahl bestätigen mit der %3[EINGABETASTE]%4. %1Du kannst den Auswahl Modus mit %3[ESC]%4 abbrechen.
Key.English: Some modules have the option to select objects on which it is apply to. %1Whenever you hear this sound you can select objects and submit the selection by pressing %3[ENTER]%4. %1You can cancle the selection mode with %3[ESCAPE]%4.

Key.Original: You can read on top what the module want you to select.
Key.French: Il est écrié au-dessus qu'est-ce que vous devez choisir.
Key.German: Oben steht jeweis geschrieben, was du auswählen sollst.
Key.Original: You can read on top what the module want you to select.

Key.English: For modules applied on objects or units it is often the case that you can either place it on one unit or place it elsewhere to apply it to multiple units.

Key.Original: Additional key assignments aviable: %1%1%2Press %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + 2x %3[LMB]%4 on a unit icon in order to remote control the AI. %1%2Press %3[Left Shift]%4 + %3[G]%4 to force passengers (including players) of a vehicle to eject (para drop for aircrafts). %1%2Press %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + %3[C]%4 in order to deep copy units. %1%2Press %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + %3[V]%4 in order to paste deep copied units. %1%2If you select a unit and press %11 it will pop smoke or countermeasure if aviable. %1%2Press %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + %3[G]%4 in order to group an advanced composition. %1%2Press %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + %3[Left Shift]%4 + %3[G]%4 in order to ungroup an advanced composition.

The execute code module is only aviable if the server allows clients using it! %1%1There are two built-in params avaiable: %1%2%3_this select 0%4 POSITION: position where the module was placed. %1%2%3_this select 1%4 OBJECT: returns ObjNull or the object on which the module was placed.
Open the %3Field Manual%4 avaiable in the escape menu for useful informations.
Key.French: Ouvrez le %3Manuel Pratique%4 dans la menu en pause pour des informations utile.
Key.German: Öffne das %Feldhandbuch%4 verfügbar im Pause-Menü für nützliche Informationen.
Key.English: Open the %3Field Manual%4 avaiable in the escape menu for informations.

Key.Original: You How to remote control a specific unit in a vehicle: %1 1) Select the unit in the object list on your left. %1 2) A new icon popes up on the vehicle corresponding to the target unit. %1 3) Press %3[Left Ctrl]%4 + 2x %3[RMB]%4 on the unit icon.
